<section id="fs-id1171472269189" class="critical-thinking">
<exercise id="fs-id1171474441002">
<problem id="fs-id1171474402745">
<para id="fs-id1171474423453">The framers of the Constitution designed the Senate to filter the output of the sometimes hasty House. Do you think this was a wise idea? Why or why not?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1171472068440">
<problem id="fs-id1171474399048">
<para id="fs-id1171474374613">Congress has consistently expanded its own power to regulate commerce among and between the states. Should Congress have this power or should the Supreme Court reel it in? Why?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1171474208014">
<problem id="fs-id1171474425237">
<para id="fs-id1171474409404">What does the trend toward descriptive representation suggest about what constituents value in their legislature? How might Congress overcome the fact that such representation does not always best serve constituents’ interests?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
<exercise id="fs-id1171472377020">
<problem id="fs-id1171474441324">
<para id="fs-id1171474223757">What factors contributed most to the transformation away from the classic legislative process and toward the new style?</para>
</problem>
</exercise>
