<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1171472084092">
<term>cloture</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1171474268946">a parliamentary process to end a debate in the Senate, as a measure against the filibuster; invoked when three-fifths of senators vote for the motion</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1171472262725">
<term>filibuster</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1171474243037">a parliamentary maneuver used in the Senate to extend debate on a piece of legislation as long as possible, typically with the intended purpose of obstructing or killing it</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1171472256964">
<term>markup</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1171472285288">the amending and voting process in a congressional committee</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
